        "message": "Patch Set 13:\n\nHi,\n\nCould you please review these changes? They refer to SDC-2499, which fixes many of the problems related to the testing of asdctool. It is part of a topic which goal is to separate the report writing and formatting logic to improve maintainability and testability.\n\nIn this change, we only focus on encapsulating the report state that used to be static in its own class. This reduces some boilerplate and removes some arguments to different functions. For now, the report's state can still be accessed, but that should be restricted in the next change by leveraging the \"Tell Don't ask\" principle.\n\nThank you in advance for your help.\n\nFrancis.",
